article.headline: Davidson's 23 points and 15 boards power Nevada past San Jose State 84-63
article.description: — Nick Davidson scored 23 points and grabbed 15 rebounds and Jarod Lucas added 20 points cruised to an 84-63 win over San Jose State on Friday night.
article.linkText: Davidson's 23 points and 15 boards power Nevada past San Jose State 84-63
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- — Nick Davidson scored 23 points and grabbed 15 rebounds and Jarod Lucas added 20 points cruised to an 84-63 win over San Jose State on Friday night. The Wolf Pack (22-6, 9-5 Mountain West) held a five-point lead at the break, but outscored the Spartans 50-34 over the final 20 minutes to earn a third-straight win. Davidson hit 8 of 9 from the floor, knocked down both of his 3-point attempts and was 5 of 7 from the line. Tre Coleman added 12 points, grabbed nine rebounds and dished eight assists. Myron Amey Jr. hit 4 of 9 from beyond the arc to lead San Jose State (9-19, 2-13) with 18 points. Latrell Davis added 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds and Alvaro Cardenas added 11 points and eight assists. Nevada travels to face No. 22 Colorado State Tuesday. San Jose State plays at No. 19 San Diego State Tuesday. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
